2026-05-27 | Check if All Rooms are Covered by WiFi

	Question
Return true if all rooms are covered.
	Key Insight
For every router position:
		mark all rooms within range as covered.
Finally:
		check whether any room remains uncovered.
	Approach
1.	Create coverage array initialized false  
2.	Traverse string:
		if s[i]=='1':
				cover range:
				[max(0,i-x) ... min(n-1,i+x)]
3.	After processing all routers:
		if any room uncovered:
				return false
4.	Otherwise:
		return true
	Time Complexity
	O(n × x)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool wifiRange(int n, string s, int x) {
        vector<bool> covered(n, false);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            if(s[i] == '1'){
                int left = max(0, i - x);
                int right = min(n - 1, i + x);
                for(int j = left; j <= right; j++){
                    covered[j] = true;
                }
            }
        }
        for(bool room : covered){
            if(!room)
                return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Each router creates a coverage interval.  
The problem reduces to:
		checking whether union of all intervals
		covers every room.
